  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI have problem syncing Rinkeby testnet since 9 Aug 2018 and encountered the same out of memory problem. It has worked previously.  I have tried couple of times and realised that it always fail around the same spot (refer to details below).  Please assist. Thank you.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nGeth Version: 1.8.15-stable\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04.5 LTS (GNU/Linux 4.14.20-041420-generic x86_64)\r\nGit Commit: 89451f7\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.10\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/lib/go-1.10\r\nRunning Ubuntu 16.04.5 LTS (GNU/Linux 4.14.20-041420-generic x86_64) on AWS T2.medium instance with 128GB\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nIt should sync but fails around the same block header 2867865 and always rollback to block header 2837951.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nINFO [09-04|04:06:44.440] Initialising Ethereum protocol versions=\"[63 62]\" network=4\r\nWARN [09-04|04:06:44.448] Head state missing, repairing chain number=2867862 hash=1e6e59…0a36ff\r\nINFO [09-04|04:07:08.704] Rewound blockchain to past state number=2837951 hash=635371…0df25a\r\nINFO [09-04|04:07:08.715] Loaded most recent local header number=**2867865** hash=6fb6b1…b8cde5 td=5382446\r\nINFO [09-04|04:07:08.716] Loaded most recent local full block number=**2837951** hash=635371…0df25a td=5338101\r\nINFO [09-04|04:07:08.716] Loaded most recent local fast block number=2867865 hash=6fb6b1…b8cde5 td=5382446\r\nINFO [09-04|04:07:08.716] Loaded local transaction journal transactions=0 dropped=0\r\nINFO [09-04|04:07:08.716] Regenerated local transaction journal transactions=0 accounts=0\r\nWARN [09-04|04:07:08.716] Blockchain not empty, fast sync disabled\r\n...\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\ngeth --rinkeby --rpc --rpcport \"8545\" --rpccorsdomain \"*\" --rpcapi=\"personal,eth,network,web3,net\" --ipcpath \"~/.ethereum/geth.ipc\"\r\n\r\n",
